Resetting Custom Settings


Reset selected custom settings banks.
1 Select I.Q. IMAGE QUALITY SETTING EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING in the shooting menu and press MENU/OK.
This assumes that you wish to reset settings for still photography. To reset movie settings, navigate to □ MOVIE SETTING in the movie menus and select EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING.
2 Highlight the desired custom set- tings bank and press MENU/OK.EDIT/SAVE CUSTOM SETTING AF CUSTOM 1 □ ASSIGNED MF CUSTOM 2 ASSIGNED CUSTOM 3 � ASSIGNED CUSTOM 4 � ASSIGNED A BACK EXIT
3 Highlight RESET CUSTOM SETTING and press MENU/OK. A confirmation dialog will be displayed.C1 CUSTOM 1 SAVE CURRENT SETTINGS EDIT/CHECK SAVE THE CHANGES RESET THE CHANGES COPY RESET CUSTOM SETTING EDIT CUSTOM NAME
4 Highlight OK and press MENU/OK. The selected bank will be reset.RESET CUSTOM SETTING C1 CUSTOM 1 RESET CUSTOM SETTING OK? RESET ALL SETTINGS TO DEFAULT OK CANCEL
